[[File:Alinco logo.svg|thumb|Alinco logo]] [[Image:Alinco 2m transceiver.jpg|thumb|right|100px|An Alinco 2-meter, [[amateur radio]] handheld transceiver.]] '''Alinco''' ( ''Alinco Inc.'') ({{tyo|5933}}) is a [[Japan]]ese manufacturer of radio and amplification equipment, and in the Japanese market, metal products, construction equipment, and exercise equipment.
Established in 1938 in [[Osaka]], [[Japan]], it also has offices in [[Tokyo]], [[Takatsuki, Osaka|Takatsuki]], manufacturing facilities in [[Toyama Prefecture|Toyama]] and [[Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo]] in Japan, and one in [[Suzhou]], [[China]].
