{{Infobox company | name = ACI Technologies, Inc. | former_name = American Competitiveness Institute | type = [[Nonprofit corporation]] | founded = 1992 | location_city = [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]] | location_country = United States | founder = Alan J. Criswell | industry = [[Electronics manufacturing services]] | website = {{URL|http://www.aciusa.org/}} }}
The '''American Competitiveness Institute''' now known as '''ACI Technologies Inc. (ACI)''' is an [[United States|American]] [[scientific research]] corporation founded by Alan J. Criswell in 1992. Located in [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]], ACI operates a {{convert|10000|sqft|m2|adj=on}} facility dedicated to the advancement of the [[electronics industry]] and research and development of various electronic manufacturing methods and materials. Early in its existence, ACI acquired a defense contract from the [[Office of Naval Research]] known as the Electronics Manufacturing Productivity Facility (EMPF).
