The '''Bedourie oven''' is an [[Australia]]n adaptation of the camp oven ([[Dutch oven]]). [[Drover (Australian)|Drovers]] working on [[Bedourie, Queensland|Bedourie]] [[Station (Australian agriculture)|Station]], in western [[Queensland]], found that the heavy [[cast iron]] camp ovens they used for cooking would often break as a result of falling from their [[pack horse]]s. The Bedourie oven was developed in response to this problem.  Made from [[Carbon steel#Mild and low carbon steel|mild steel]], it was lighter and less brittle than cast iron, and would not break if dropped.

