A '''Gamma loop''' is a loop about [[alloy]]s of steel. When adding additives to iron, a stable zone of [[austenite]] may increase or decrease. Some additives decrease the Austenite stable zone. In this case, the [[phase boundary]] becomes a loop. Adding Gamma loop additives prevents the steel from suffering [[phase transition]] to other solid states.<ref>{{cite book |title=Handbook of Materials Selection |editor=Myer Kurz |page=44 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gWg-rchM700C&pg=PA44&lpg=PA44&dq=gamma+loop+steel+-medicine+-medical&source=bl&ots=xHKdqDRBrj&sig=x0Kpr_e9LJZ0E-RE7JgKRLuWIrs&hl=en&sa=X&ei=AL-zUumvGs_woAS_qIKABQ&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=gamma%20loop%20steel%20-medicine%20-medical&f=false |accessdate=December 19, 2013}}</ref>

